Mutual Rank eQTL overlap

Background

Rob Baker et al fit growth parameters to B. rapa growth data and then used those to do function-value-trait QTL mapping.

I used those same parameters and queried a mutual rank (MR) gene expression network to find genes that were in a networks associated with these growth paramters. This was done separeately for the CR and UN environments. I looked for overalp between those MR-associated genes and growth parameters.

The goal now is to find the trans eQTL for each of the MR-growth associated genes and ask if the trans eQTL overlap with the growth/function-value QTL. I think I am only going to take the top eQTL for each.

Methodology

For each gene in a MR network with a growth parameter query the eQTL database to find its trans eQTL regions. Then compare overlaps between those and the growth QTL.

Find eQTL intervals

CR data

Get the scanone data in a nice format for summarizing and plotting

scanone_CR_gather <- scanone_imp_CR %>%
  gather(key = gene, value = LOD, -chr, -pos) %>%
  semi_join(MR_CR_genes,by=c("gene"="name")) # only keep genes in MR networks

plot eQTL peaks…

pl.CR <- scanone_CR_gather %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=pos,y=LOD,color=gene)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_hline(aes(yintercept=4),lty=2,lwd=.5,alpha=.5) +
  facet_grid( ~ chr, scales="free") +
  theme(strip.text.y = element_text(angle=0), axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90)) +
  ggtitle("MR gene eQTL")
pl.CR

ggsave("MR gene eQTL CR.pdf",width=12,height=8)
sig_chromosomes_CR <- scanone_CR_gather %>%
  group_by(gene,chr) %>%
  summarize(pos=pos[which.max(LOD)],LOD=max(LOD)) %>%
  filter(LOD > 4)
sig_chromosomes_CR

now for each significant chromosome/trait combo run bayesint

bayesint_list_CR <- apply(sig_chromosomes_CR,1,function(hit) {
  result <- bayesint(scanone_imp_CR[c("chr","pos",hit["gene"])], 
                     chr=hit["chr"], 
                     lodcolumn = 1,
                     expandtomarkers = TRUE
  )
  colnames(result)[3] <- "LOD"
  result
})
names(bayesint_list_CR) <- sig_chromosomes_CR$gene
bayesint_list_CR <- lapply(bayesint_list_CR,function(x) x %>% 
                             as.data.frame() %>%
                             rownames_to_column(var="markername") %>%
                             mutate(chr=as.character(chr))
)
bayesint_result_CR <- as.tibble(bind_rows(bayesint_list_CR,.id="gene")) %>% 
  select(gene,chr,pos,markername,LOD) %>%
  separate(markername,into=c("chr1","Mbp"),sep="x", convert=TRUE) %>%
  group_by(gene,chr) %>%
  summarize(start=min(Mbp),end=max(Mbp),min_eQTL_LOD=min(LOD),max_eQTL_LOD=max(LOD)) %>%
  #for the high QTL peaks the interval width is 0.  That is overly precise and need to widen those.
  mutate(start=ifelse(start==end,max(0,start-20000),start), end=ifelse(start==end,end+20000,end))
bayesint_result_CR

bayesint_list_UN <- apply(sig_chromosomes_UN,1,function(hit) {
  result <- bayesint(scanone_imp_UN[c("chr","pos",hit["gene"])], 
                     chr=hit["chr"], 
                     lodcolumn = 1,
                     expandtomarkers = TRUE
  )
  colnames(result)[3] <- "LOD"
  result
})
names(bayesint_list_UN) <- sig_chromosomes_UN$gene
bayesint_list_UN <- lapply(bayesint_list_UN,function(x) x %>% 
                             as.data.frame(stringsAsFactors=FALSE) %>%
                             rownames_to_column(var="markername") %>%
                             mutate(chr=as.character(chr))
)
bayesint_result_UN <- as.tibble(bind_rows(bayesint_list_UN,.id="gene")) %>% 
  select(gene,chr,pos,markername,LOD) %>%
  separate(markername,into=c("chr1","Mbp"),sep="x", convert=TRUE) %>%
  group_by(gene,chr) %>%
  summarize(start=min(Mbp),end=max(Mbp),min_eQTL_LOD=min(LOD),max_eQTL_LOD=max(LOD)) %>%
  #for the high QTL peaks the interval width is 0.  That is overly precise and need to widen those.
  mutate(start=ifelse(start==end,max(0,start-20000),start), end=ifelse(start==end,end+20000,end))

CR

CR_annotated <- lapply(1:nrow(bayesint_result_CR),function(row) {
  qtl <- bayesint_result_CR[row,]
  subset(BrapaAnnotation, chrom==qtl$chr &
           start >= qtl$start &
           end <= qtl$end) 
}
)
names(CR_annotated) <- bayesint_result_CR$gene
CR_annotated <- bind_rows(CR_annotated,.id="MR_gene") %>%
  left_join(bayesint_result_CR,by=c("MR_gene"="gene","chrom"="chr")) %>% #get eQTL LOD
    left_join(MR_CR_genes,by=c("MR_gene"="name")) %>% # get cutoff
  rename(eQTL_candidate=name)
CR_annotated_small <- CR_annotated %>% select(MR_gene,MR_Cutoff,eQTL_candidate,ends_with("LOD"))
CR_annotated_small

given bayesint results, find overlaps with CR growth QTL

CR_MReQTL_QTL_combined <- inner_join(QTLgenes,CR_annotated_small,by=c("name"="eQTL_candidate")) %>%
  select(.id, MR_gene, MR_Cutoff, ends_with("LOD"), everything()) %>%
  arrange(.id,desc(max_eQTL_LOD)) %>%
  rename(eQTL_candidate=name)
CR_MReQTL_QTL_combined
CR_MReQTL_QTL_combined_small <- CR_MReQTL_QTL_combined %>% filter(!duplicated(eQTL_candidate)) %>%
  select(-MR_gene,-MR_Cutoff) 
CR_MReQTL_QTL_combined_small
